You don't need to do this. Just return `tomlli; python_version < "3.11"` from the `get_requires_for_build_*()` hooks.
This library is API-compatible with `tomllib` and is maintained by a few CPython Core Devs ([PEP 680](https://peps.python.org/pep-0680/) authors/sponsors). In fact, `tomllib` grew out of `tomli` so it's a very safe bet: https://realpython.com/python311-tomllib/#read-toml-with-tomllib.

```suggestion
    try:
        import tomllib
    except ImportError:
        import tomli as tomllib  # is in standard library from 3.11 onwards

    with open(filename, "rb") as f:
        return tomllib.load(f)
```
